@@rThe Cinderteeth Mountains@@N

  A discontinuous volcanic arc of broken tooth-ridges rising west to
northeast across the continent. The mountains do not erase history --
they @@rselect@@N what survives by making logistics, memory, and legitimacy
fail together.

  Before the Keepers arrived with survey tablets, the @@yVentspeakers@@N
maintained the range. They read volcanic vents as oracular instruments,
placing polished name-stones at vent mouths and building observation
platforms over active gas releases. Their methodology was empirical
geology encoded in ritual vocabulary -- pattern recognition passed
across generations. When the @@eSpirebound Conclave@@N occupied the Western
Fold for its mountain sanctum, the Ventspeakers were displaced without
negotiation. Their sacred fire-pits went cold.

  The Conclave built its research stronghold in the isolation of the
peaks, where distance made accountability impossible. They embedded
crystal resonance-monitoring anchors at fault intersections and pursued
the @@lPrism Thesis@@N -- experiments binding nature spirits to crystal
matrices in distant forests. When the sanctum collapsed, neither
crystals nor consequences were retrieved.

  Six subregions define the range. The @@rEmber Crown@@N holds the highest
calderas, wreathed in vent-gas and glassfall. The @@eBellspine@@N is a
fracture-scarred mid-ridge where deep-frequency vibrations travel
through stone, producing the bell tones that give it its name. The
@@yChalkwind Saddles@@N serve as the primary commercial transit corridor.
The @@dGlasswash Fans@@N produce obsidian and sulfur for distant markets.
The @@dBlackstep Footholds@@N mark the contested boundary between mountain
law and civic jurisdiction.

  The @@rAshfall catastrophe@@N -- when eruptions sent ash clouds across
the continent -- devastated Kowloon's delta, poisoned the Great
Northern Forest's streams, and intensified the Eastern Desert's
drought. The same deep fault system couples mountain seismic events
to tremors in the oasis-pyramid corridor, meaning a shudder in the
Cinderteeth can trigger consequences hundreds of miles away.

  The @@dAsh Cult@@N endures in scattered cells, reading eruptions as divine
verdicts against civic corruption -- a degraded echo of Ventspeaker
doctrine stripped of its empirical foundations. They are the mountains'
theological inheritors, fervent and untestable where the Ventspeakers
were observant and correctable.
